White blood cell (leukocyte) count
Additional Notes: Result of "White Blood Cell Count" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. White blood count is the number of leukocytes. Analyser operating range was 0 to 9x10^11 cells/Litre. Typical reference range is 3.5x10^9 to 9.6x10^9 cells/Litre.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Red blood cell (erythrocyte) count
Additional Notes: Result of "Red Blood Cell Count" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Red blood cells is the number of erythrocytes. Analyser operating range was 0 to 2x10^13 cells/Litre. Typical reference range is 3.9x10^12 to 5.5x10^12 cells/Litre.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Haemoglobin concentration
Additional Notes: Result of "Haemoglobin Concentration" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Analyser operating range was 0 to 99.9g/dL Typical reference range is 12.1 to 16.3g/dL

Detailed Description (as applicable): Haematocrit percentage
Additional Notes: Result of "Haematocrit" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Haematocrit Percentage is the relative volume of packed erythrocytes to whole blood, computed by the formula: (red blood cells x mean corpuscular volume) / 10. Analyser operating range was 0 to 99.9% Typical reference range is 35.4 to 47.2%

Detailed Description (as applicable): Mean corpuscular volume
Additional Notes: Result of "Mean Corpuscular Volume" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Mean Corpuscular Haemoglobin Concentration (pg) is the weight of hemoglobin in the average erythrocyte, computed by the formula: MCH = (hemoglobin/red blood cells) x 10.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Mean corpuscular haemoglobin
Additional Notes: Result of "Mean Corpuscular Haemoglobin" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Mean corpuscular haemoglobin concentration
Additional Notes: Result of "Mean Corpuscular Haemoglobin Concentration" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Mean Corpuscular Haemoglobin Concentration (g/dL) is the average weight of haemoglobin in a measured dilution, computed by the formula: (haemoglobin/haematocrit) x 100.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Red blood cell (erythrocyte) distribution width
Additional Notes: Result of "Red Distribution Width" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Red blood cell Distribution Width is the size distribution spread of the erythrocyte population derived from the red blood cell histogram. It is the coefficient of variation (CV) expressed in % of the red blood cell size distribution.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Platelet count
Additional Notes: Result of "Platelet Count" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Platelet count is the number of thrombocytes derived from the platelet histogram.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Platelet crit
Additional Notes: Result of "Platelet Crit" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Platelet Crit is a computed value that represents the platelet packed cell volume.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Mean platelet (thrombocyte) volume
Additional Notes: Result of "Mean Platelet Volume" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Mean Platelet Volume is the average volume of individual platelets derived from the platelet histogram.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Platelet distribution width
Additional Notes: Result of "Platelet Distribution Width" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Platelet Distribution Width is the coefficient of variation of platelet size.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Lymphocyte count
Additional Notes: Result of "Lymphocytes Number" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Lymphocyte count is the proportion of ( lymphoctyes / 100 ) x white blood cell count

Detailed Description (as applicable): Monocyte count
Additional Notes: Result of "Monocytes Number" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Monocyte count is the proportion of ( monoctyes / 100 ) x white blood cell count.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Neutrophill count
Additional Notes: Result of "Neutrophils Number" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Neutrophils count is the proportion of ( neutrophils / 100 ) x white blood cell count.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Lymphocyte percentage
Additional Notes: Result of "Lymphocytes Percentage" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Lymphocytes (Percentage) is calculated as the proportion of lymphocytes in the leukocytes.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Monocyte percentage
Additional Notes: Result of "Monocytes Percentage" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Monocytes (percentage) is calculated as the proportion of monocytes in the leukocytes.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Neutrophill percentage
Additional Notes: Result of "Neutrophils Percentage" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Neutrophils (Percentage) is calculated as the proportion of neutrophils in the leukocytes.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Eosinophill percentage
Additional Notes: Result of "Eosinophils Percentage" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Eosinophils (Percentage) is calculated as the proportion of eosinophils in the leukocytes.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Basophill percentage
Additional Notes: Result of "Basophils Percentage" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Basophils (Percentage) is calculated as the proportion of basophils in the leukocytes.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Reticulocyte percentage
Additional Notes: Result of "Reticulocytes Percentage" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Reticulocytes (Percentage) is the number of reticulocytes as a percentage of red blood cells.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Reticulocyte count
Additional Notes: Result of "Reticulocytes Number" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Reticulocytes count is computed from the reticulocyte per cent multiplied by the red blood cell count.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Mean reticulocyte volume
Additional Notes: Result of "Mean Reticulocytes Volume" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Mean Reticulocytes volume is the average volume of all reticulocytes, calculated from the reticulocytes (percentage).

Detailed Description (as applicable): Mean sphered cell volume
Additional Notes: Result of "Mean Sphered Cells Volume" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit.

Detailed Description (as applicable): Immature reticulocyte fraction
Additional Notes: Result of "Immature Reticulocytes Fraction" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. Immature Reticulocytes Fraction (Percentage) is an indication of new reticulocyte synthesis and is calculated from the reticulocytes (Percentage) as the total number of reticulocyte events in the outermost light scattering region, corresponding to immature reticulocytes, relative to the total number of reticulocytes and is reported as this ratio.

Detailed Description (as applicable): High light scatter reticulocyte percentage
Additional Notes: Result of "High Light Scatter Reticulocytes Percentage" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. High Light Scatter Reticulocytes (Percentage) is computed as: (HLR / Total Erythrocytes) x 100.

Detailed Description (as applicable): High light scatter reticulocyte count
Additional Notes: Result of "High Light Scatter Reticulocytes Number" assay, performed on blood sample, obtained from UK Biobank assessment centre visit. High Light Scatter Reticulocytes Count is calculated as: (HLR / Total Erythrocytes) x red blood cells
